{
  "texts": [
    "Despite their potential, LLMs have demonstrated certain biases (Gallegos et al., 2309; Jones & Steinhardt, 2022) and are prone to errors (Tlili et al., 2023), particularly in the realms of physics and mathematics (Krupp et al., 2024 (Krupp et al.,, 2312;; S. Küchemann et al., 2023).",
    "Ensuring the controllability, explainability, and lawful use of LLMs presents a significant challenge.",
    "Additionally, ethical considerations such as the potential for bias and the broader impact of these models must be carefully addressed (Kasneci et al., 2023; S. Küchemann, K. E. Avila, Y. Dinc, C. Hortmann, N. Revenga, V. Ruf, N. Stausberg, S. Steinert, F. Fischer, M. Fischer, et al., 2024).",
    "Nevertheless, the continuous evolution and refinement of LLMs are gradually addressing these issues, bringing us closer to the reality of AI-powered tutors in educational settings (Hemachandran et al., 2022; Jeon & Lee, 2023).",
    "Beyond the acknowledged challenges that LLMs present in the educational sector, it is known that simply providing information via an interface like ChatGPT is insufficient for learning due to the non-linear process of knowledge acquisition (Everwijn et al., 1993; Wittrock, 2000)."
  ]
}